'''分布式块存储'''是一种[[電腦數據存貯器|電腦數據存貯器]]体系结构，其数据跨多个物理服务器存储在卷（称为块<sup><ref name="[1]">{{tsl|en|Gerrit Anne Blaauw|}}; [[佛瑞德·布魯克斯|佛瑞德·布魯克斯]]; {{tsl|en|Werner Buchholz|}} (1962), [http://archive.computerhistory.org/resources/text/IBM/Stretch/pdfs/Buchholz_102636426.pdf "4: Natural Data Units" (PDF)] {{Wayback|url=http://archive.computerhistory.org/resources/text/IBM/Stretch/pdfs/Buchholz_102636426.pdf |date=20170403014651 }}, in {{tsl|en|Werner Buchholz|}} (ed.), Planning a Computer System – Project Stretch, [[标普全球|McGraw-Hill Book Company, Inc.]] / The Maple Press Company, York, PA., pp. 39–40, [[美国国会图书馆控制号|LCCN]] [https://lccn.loc.gov/61-10466 61-10466], [https://web.archive.org/web/20170403014651/http://archive.computerhistory.org/resources/text/IBM/Stretch/pdfs/Buchholz_102636426.pdf archived (PDF)] from the original on 2017-04-03, retrieved 2017-04-03, […] Terms used here to describe the structure imposed by the machine design, in addition to [[位元|bit]], are listed below.
[[字节|Byte]] denotes a group of bits used to encode a [[字符_(计算机科学)|字符 (计算机科学)]], or the number of bits transmitted in parallel to and from input-output units. A term other than character is used here because a given character may be represented in different applications by more than one code, and different codes may use different numbers of bits (i.e., different byte sizes). In input-output transmission the grouping of bits may be completely arbitrary and have no relation to actual characters. (The term is coined from bite, but respelled to avoid accidental mutation to bit.)
A word consists of the number of data bits transmitted in parallel from or to memory in one memory cycle. [[Word_size|Word size]] is thus defined as a structural property of the memory. (The term [[字_(计算机)|字 (计算机)]] was coined for this purpose by the designers of the Bull {{tsl|en|Bull Gamma 60|}} [fr] computer.)
Block refers to the number of words transmitted to or from an input-output unit in response to a single input-output instruction. Block size is a structural property of an input-output unit; it may have been fixed by the design or left to be varied by the program. […]</ref></sup>）中，这与其他存储体系结构（如将数据作为文件层次结构管理数据的文件系统和将数据作为文件结构进行管理的对象存储）相反对象。常见的分布式块存储系统是存储区域网络（{{tsl|en|SAN|}}）。

== 分布式存储 ==
与集中式存储相反，分布式存储通常采用存储单元集群的形式，并具有在集群节点之间进行数据同步和协调的机制。分布式存储最初是由[[Google|Google]]提出的，其目的是通过廉价服务器解决大规模，高并发情况下的Web访问问题。

分布式存储具有几个优点<sup><ref name="[2]">[https://cloudian.com/guides/data-backup/distributed-storage/ Distributed Storage: What’s Inside Amazon S3?] {{Wayback|url=https://cloudian.com/guides/data-backup/distributed-storage/ |date=20201124124037 }} cloudian</ref></sup>：

* 可扩展性-支持通过在系统中添加或删除存储单元来水平扩展存储系统。
* 冗余-在多台服务器之间存储相同数据的复制，以实现高可用性， 备份和灾难恢复目的。
* 节省成本 -可以使用更便宜的商品服务器以低成本存储大量 数据。
* 性能-在某些情况下，性能比单个服务器更好，例如，它可以将数据存储在离其使用者更近的位置，或者允许大规模并行访问大文件。

== 块存储 ==
块存储可将数据与用户环境分离，并允许将数据分布在多个环境<sup><ref name="[3]">[https://www.ibm.com/cloud/learn/block-storage What is Block Storage?] {{Wayback|url=https://www.ibm.com/cloud/learn/block-storage |date=20210207134906 }} IBM</ref>
</sup>中。存储被组织为具有唯一标识符的块，通过它们可以将其存储和检索为单独的硬盘驱动器，并且操作系统可以连接到它们。这是存储，使用和管理数据的有效且可靠的方式。块存储几乎可以用于任何类型的应用程序，包括但不限于数据库存储和虚拟化平台存储。

通常通过[[ISCSI|ISCSI]]， [[光纤通道|光纤通道]] 或以太网光纤通道（[[乙太網路光纖通道標準|FCoE]]）协议访问存储块 。块存储为任务关键型应用的高性能 和可提供高I/O性能和低延迟。它通常在 [[存储区域网络|存储区域网络]]环境中代替文件存储。

